    "acceptance_critic_gate_surface": "# Lessons Acceptance Critic Criteria

This file owns what Lessons Acceptance Critic checks before work moves on.

Use it with the governing workflow and any supporting standards for this gate.

<a id="what-the-critic-judges"></a>
## What the critic judges

Judge whether the packet chain is trustworthy and the quality bar still holds.

- Checks that must pass: LESSON_PLAN.md, Quality Bar
- Read before acting: Quality Bar
",
    "authoritative_workflow": "# Lessons Workflow

This is the top-level workflow for Lessons.

Use this file for lane order, same-issue handoff, and owner routing.

<a id="owner-map"></a>
## Owner Map

Use this section to understand the represented workflow order for the current setup.

1. Section Dossier Engineer: Define what the section teaches, what it does not teach, and the receipts behind those calls.
2. Lessons Lesson Architect: Turn the upstream dossier into a lesson plan with explicit teaching burden and deferred work.

This section currently documents the Lessons Lesson Architect lane.

- Read before acting: Packet Shape
- Read before acting: Quality Bar
- Required inputs: Section Dossier
- Support inputs: Packet Shape Standard, Quality Bar Standard, Lessons Structured Doctrine Requirements
- Interim artifacts: none
- Outputs the next owner may trust: LESSON_PLAN.md
- Stop line: Stop once the lesson plan is stable enough for the critic to judge.
- Hand off to gate: Lessons Acceptance Critic

